CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg. B6 reads: "Symposium On Civil Rights - The young people's ushers board of Central Baptist Church sponsored a symposium and tea recently at the church. The topic under panel discussion was "Youth and Civil Rights."  The participants on the program were, left to right: Kaye Crosby, Ebenezer Baptist; Donald Davis, Carnegie; Donald Register, program chairman; Dorothy Williams, mistress of ceremonies; Sarah Plowden, moderator; Arnita Pyles and Allen Johnson, Central Baptist, and Anderson Bray, Ebenezer Baptist. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Civil Rights symposium participants, from left: Kaye Crosby, Donald Davis, Donald Register, Dorothy Williams, Sarah Plowden, Arnita Pyles, Allen Johnson, and Anderson Bray, standing in Central Baptist Church with tables with large umbrellas
